{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":502,"text":"Technology can change our understanding of nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4693,"text":"Take for example the case of lions."},{"time":7844,"text":"For centuries, it's been said that female lions"},{"time":10014,"text":"do all of the hunting out in the open savanna,"},{"time":12743,"text":"and male lions do nothing until it's time for dinner."},{"time":16724,"text":"You've heard this too, I can tell."},{"time":19736,"text":"Well recently, I led an airborne mapping campaign"},{"time":22322,"text":"in the Kruger National Park in South Africa."},{"time":24994,"text":"Our colleagues put GPS tracking collars"},{"time":27586,"text":"on male and female lions,"},{"time":29183,"text":"and we mapped their hunting behavior"},{"time":30791,"text":"from the air."},{"time":32239,"text":"The lower left shows a lion sizing up"},{"time":34905,"text":"a herd of impala for a kill,"},{"time":36917,"text":"and the right shows what I call"},{"time":38486,"text":"the lion viewshed."},{"time":40349,"text":"That's how far the lion can see in all directions"},{"time":42971,"text":"until his or her view is obstructed by vegetation."},{"time":47146,"text":"And what we found"},{"time":48587,"text":"is that male lions are not the lazy hunters"},{"time":51093,"text":"we thought them to be."},{"time":52617,"text":"They just use a different strategy."},{"time":54754,"text":"Whereas the female lions hunt"},{"time":56506,"text":"out in the open savanna"},{"time":57638,"text":"over long distances, usually during the day,"},{"time":60299,"text":"male lions use an ambush strategy"},{"time":63309,"text":"in dense vegetation, and often at night."},{"time":67042,"text":"This video shows the actual hunting viewsheds"},{"time":70048,"text":"of male lions on the left"},{"time":71913,"text":"and females on the right."},{"time":73902,"text":"Red and darker colors show more dense vegetation,"},{"time":76458,"text":"and the white are wide open spaces."},{"time":78573,"text":"And this is the viewshed right literally at the eye level"},{"time":81673,"text":"of hunting male and female lions."},{"time":84203,"text":"All of a sudden, you get a very clear understanding"},{"time":86532,"text":"of the very spooky conditions under which"},{"time":89385,"text":"male lions do their hunting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91465,"text":"I bring up this example to begin,"},{"time":92961,"text":"because it emphasizes how little\nwe know about nature."},{"time":97429,"text":"There's been a huge amount of work done so far"},{"time":100104,"text":"to try to slow down our losses of tropical forests,"},{"time":103732,"text":"and we are losing our forests at a rapid rate,"},{"time":105681,"text":"as shown in red on the slide."},{"time":107595,"text":"I find it ironic that we're doing so much,"},{"time":109935,"text":"yet these areas are fairly unknown to science."},{"time":113568,"text":"So how can we save what we don't understand?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":116225,"text":"Now I'm a global ecologist and an Earth explorer"},{"time":118887,"text":"with a background in physics and chemistry"},{"time":120578,"text":"and biology and a lot of other boring subjects,"},{"time":123782,"text":"but above all, I'm obsessed with what we don't know"},{"time":126784,"text":"about our planet."},{"time":128496,"text":"So I created this,"},{"time":130170,"text":"the Carnegie Airborne Observatory, or CAO."},{"time":133447,"text":"It may look like a plane with a fancy paint job,"},{"time":135504,"text":"but I packed it with over 1,000 kilos"},{"time":138264,"text":"of high-tech sensors, computers,"},{"time":140700,"text":"and a very motivated staff"},{"time":142911,"text":"of Earth scientists and pilots."},{"time":145380,"text":"Two of our instruments are very unique:"},{"time":147240,"text":"one is called an imaging spectrometer"},{"time":148994,"text":"that can actually measure the chemical composition"},{"time":150856,"text":"of plants as we fly over them."},{"time":153785,"text":"Another one is a set of lasers,"},{"time":155711,"text":"very high-powered lasers,"},{"time":157442,"text":"that fire out of the bottom of the plane,"},{"time":159402,"text":"sweeping across the ecosystem"},{"time":161274,"text":"and measuring it at nearly 500,000 times per second"},{"time":165371,"text":"in high-resolution 3D."},{"time":167849,"text":"Here's an image of the Golden Gate Bridge"},{"time":169833,"text":"in San Francisco, not far from where I live."},{"time":172005,"text":"Although we flew straight over this bridge,"},{"time":173808,"text":"we imaged it in 3D, captured its color"},{"time":175464,"text":"in just a few seconds."},{"time":177511,"text":"But the real power of the CAO"},{"time":179606,"text":"is its ability to capture the actual building blocks"},{"time":181781,"text":"of ecosystems."},{"time":183550,"text":"This is a small town in the Amazon,"},{"time":185249,"text":"imaged with the CAO."},{"time":186864,"text":"We can slice through our data"},{"time":188603,"text":"and see, for example, the 3D structure"},{"time":190867,"text":"of the vegetation and the buildings,"},{"time":193200,"text":"or we can use the chemical information"},{"time":195109,"text":"to actually figure out how fast the plants are growing"},{"time":197840,"text":"as we fly over them."},{"time":199183,"text":"The hottest pinks are the fastest-growing plants."},{"time":202669,"text":"And we can see biodiversity in ways"},{"time":204586,"text":"that you never could have imagined."},{"time":206745,"text":"This is what a rainforest might look like"},{"time":208296,"text":"as you fly over it in a hot air balloon."},{"time":210503,"text":"This is how we see a rainforest,"},{"time":212597,"text":"in kaleidoscopic color that tells us"},{"time":214942,"text":"that there are many species living with one another."},{"time":217884,"text":"But you have to remember that these trees"},{"time":219808,"text":"are literally bigger than whales,"},{"time":222104,"text":"and what that means is that\nthey're impossible to understand"},{"time":225016,"text":"just by walking on the ground below them."},{"time":227991,"text":"So our imagery is 3D, it's chemical, it's biological,"},{"time":232629,"text":"and this tells us not only the species"},{"time":234387,"text":"that are living in the canopy,"},{"time":236271,"text":"but it tells us a lot of information"},{"time":238191,"text":"about the rest of the species\nthat occupy the rainforest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241767,"text":"Now I created the CAO"},{"time":243898,"text":"in order to answer questions that have proven"},{"time":246037,"text":"extremely challenging to answer\nfrom any other vantage point,"},{"time":249389,"text":"such as from the ground, or from satellite sensors."},{"time":252266,"text":"I want to share three of those\nquestions with you today."},{"time":255503,"text":"The first questions is,"},{"time":257210,"text":"how do we manage our carbon reserves"},{"time":258939,"text":"in tropical forests?"},{"time":261695,"text":"Tropical forests contain a huge\namount of carbon in the trees,"},{"time":265254,"text":"and we need to keep that carbon in those forests"},{"time":267668,"text":"if we're going to avoid any further global warming."},{"time":271082,"text":"Unfortunately, global carbon emissions"},{"time":273308,"text":"from deforestation"},{"time":275071,"text":"now equals the global transportation sector."},{"time":278246,"text":"That's all ships, airplanes, trains \nand automobiles combined."},{"time":282549,"text":"So it's understandable that policy negotiators"},{"time":285640,"text":"have been working hard to reduce deforestation,"},{"time":288128,"text":"but they're doing it on landscapes"},{"time":289999,"text":"that are hardly known to science."},{"time":292138,"text":"If you don't know where the carbon is exactly,"},{"time":294499,"text":"in detail, how can you know what you're losing?"},{"time":297351,"text":"Basically, we need a high-tech accounting system."},{"time":301408,"text":"With our system, we're able to see the carbon stocks"},{"time":303724,"text":"of tropical forests in utter detail."},{"time":306522,"text":"The red shows, obviously,\nclosed-canopy tropical forest,"},{"time":309377,"text":"and then you see the cookie cutting,"},{"time":311395,"text":"or the cutting of the forest in yellows and greens."},{"time":315302,"text":"It's like cutting a cake except this cake"},{"time":318125,"text":"is about whale deep."},{"time":320324,"text":"And yet, we can zoom in and see the forest"},{"time":322292,"text":"and the trees at the same time."},{"time":324305,"text":"And what's amazing is, even though we flew"},{"time":326507,"text":"very high above this forest,"},{"time":328784,"text":"later on in analysis, we can go in"},{"time":330687,"text":"and actually experience the treetrops,"},{"time":332907,"text":"leaf by leaf, branch by branch,"},{"time":335254,"text":"just as the other species that live in this forest"},{"time":338761,"text":"experience it along with the trees themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341578,"text":"We've been using the technology to explore"},{"time":343744,"text":"and to actually put out the first carbon geographies"},{"time":346614,"text":"in high resolution"},{"time":348228,"text":"in faraway places like the Amazon Basin"},{"time":350474,"text":"and not-so-faraway places like the United States"},{"time":352761,"text":"and Central America."},{"time":354494,"text":"What I'm going to do is I'm going to take you\non a high-resolution, first-time tour"},{"time":357994,"text":"of the carbon landscapes of Peru and then Panama."},{"time":361923,"text":"The colors are going to be going from red to blue."},{"time":364685,"text":"Red is extremely high carbon stocks,"},{"time":366679,"text":"your largest cathedral forests you can imagine,"},{"time":369218,"text":"and blue are very low carbon stocks."},{"time":371460,"text":"And let me tell you, Peru alone is an amazing place,"},{"time":373894,"text":"totally unknown in terms of its carbon geography"},{"time":376283,"text":"until today."},{"time":377869,"text":"We can fly to this area in northern Peru"},{"time":379715,"text":"and see super high carbon stocks in red,"},{"time":381851,"text":"and the Amazon River and floodplain"},{"time":383340,"text":"cutting right through it."},{"time":385085,"text":"We can go to an area of utter devastation"},{"time":386983,"text":"caused by deforestation in blue,"},{"time":388818,"text":"and the virus of deforestation\nspreading out in orange."},{"time":392260,"text":"We can also fly to the southern Andes"},{"time":394944,"text":"to see the tree line and see exactly how"},{"time":396794,"text":"the carbon geography ends"},{"time":398710,"text":"as we go up into the mountain system."},{"time":401416,"text":"And we can go to the biggest swamp\nin the western Amazon."},{"time":404321,"text":"It's a watery dreamworld"},{"time":405694,"text":"akin to Jim Cameron's \"Avatar.\""},{"time":408040,"text":"We can go to one of the smallest tropical countries,"},{"time":411344,"text":"Panama, and see also a huge range"},{"time":413701,"text":"of carbon variation,"},{"time":415263,"text":"from high in red to low in blue."},{"time":417264,"text":"Unfortunately, most of the carbon\nis lost in the lowlands,"},{"time":420196,"text":"but what you see that's left,"},{"time":421742,"text":"in terms of high carbon stocks in greens and reds,"},{"time":424475,"text":"is the stuff that's up in the mountains."},{"time":426589,"text":"One interesting exception to this"},{"time":428947,"text":"is right in the middle of your screen."},{"time":430563,"text":"You're seeing the buffer zone\naround the Panama Canal."},{"time":433207,"text":"That's in the reds and yellows."},{"time":435120,"text":"The canal authorities are using force"},{"time":436860,"text":"to protect their watershed and global commerce."},{"time":439975,"text":"This kind of carbon mapping"},{"time":441465,"text":"has transformed conservation"},{"time":443383,"text":"and resource policy development."},{"time":444979,"text":"It's really advancing our ability to save forests"},{"time":447339,"text":"and to curb climate change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449714,"text":"My second question: How do we\nprepare for climate change"},{"time":453145,"text":"in a place like the Amazon rainforest?"},{"time":455291,"text":"Let me tell you, I spend a lot of time"},{"time":456944,"text":"in these places, and we're seeing\nthe climate changing already."},{"time":460169,"text":"Temperatures are increasing,"},{"time":461781,"text":"and what's really happening is\nwe're getting a lot of droughts,"},{"time":464413,"text":"recurring droughts."},{"time":466070,"text":"The 2010 mega-drought is shown here"},{"time":467887,"text":"with red showing an area\nabout the size of Western Europe."},{"time":471337,"text":"The Amazon was so dry in 2010"},{"time":473599,"text":"that even the main stem of the Amazon river itself"},{"time":476001,"text":"dried up partially, as you see in the photo"},{"time":478150,"text":"in the lower portion of the slide."},{"time":481556,"text":"What we found is that in very remote areas,"},{"time":484726,"text":"these droughts are having a big negative impact"},{"time":487472,"text":"on tropical forests."},{"time":489060,"text":"For example, these are all of the dead trees in red"},{"time":491780,"text":"that suffered mortality following the 2010 drought."},{"time":494841,"text":"This area happens to be on the border"},{"time":496718,"text":"of Peru and Brazil,"},{"time":498117,"text":"totally unexplored,"},{"time":499653,"text":"almost totally unknown scientifically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502456,"text":"So what we think, as Earth scientists,"},{"time":504922,"text":"is species are going to have to migrate"},{"time":506881,"text":"with climate change from the east in Brazil"},{"time":509673,"text":"all the way west into the Andes"},{"time":511737,"text":"and up into the mountains"},{"time":513210,"text":"in order to minimize their\nexposure to climate change."},{"time":516746,"text":"One of the problems with this is that humans"},{"time":518754,"text":"are taking apart the western Amazon as we speak."},{"time":521779,"text":"Look at this 100-square-kilometer gash"},{"time":523888,"text":"in the forest created by gold miners."},{"time":526790,"text":"You see the forest in green in 3D,"},{"time":529068,"text":"and you see the effects of gold mining"},{"time":530902,"text":"down below the soil surface."},{"time":533441,"text":"Species have nowhere to migrate\nin a system like this, obviously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537900,"text":"If you haven't been to the Amazon, you should go."},{"time":540552,"text":"It's an amazing experience every time,"},{"time":542590,"text":"no matter where you go."},{"time":544133,"text":"You're going to probably see it this way, on a river."},{"time":547529,"text":"But what happens is a lot of times"},{"time":549293,"text":"the rivers hide what's really going on"},{"time":551145,"text":"back in the forest itself."},{"time":553910,"text":"We flew over this same river,"},{"time":555624,"text":"imaged the system in 3D."},{"time":557464,"text":"The forest is on the left."},{"time":559280,"text":"And then we can digitally remove the forest"},{"time":561266,"text":"and see what's going on below the canopy."},{"time":563725,"text":"And in this case, we found gold mining activity,"},{"time":566175,"text":"all of it illegal,"},{"time":567412,"text":"set back away from the river's edge,"},{"time":569608,"text":"as you'll see in those strange pockmarks"},{"time":571512,"text":"coming up on your screen on the right."},{"time":573539,"text":"Don't worry, we're working with the authorities"},{"time":575868,"text":"to deal with this and many, many other problems"},{"time":578319,"text":"in the region."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580929,"text":"So in order to put together a conservation plan"},{"time":583984,"text":"for these unique, important corridors"},{"time":585724,"text":"like the western Amazon\nand the Andes Amazon corridor,"},{"time":588711,"text":"we have to start making"},{"time":590875,"text":"geographically explicit plans now."},{"time":593283,"text":"How do we do that if we don't know\nthe geography of biodiversity in the region,"},{"time":597258,"text":"if it's so unknown to science?"},{"time":598953,"text":"So what we've been doing is using"},{"time":600817,"text":"the laser-guided spectroscopy from the CAO"},{"time":603790,"text":"to map for the first time the biodiversity"},{"time":606014,"text":"of the Amazon rainforest."},{"time":607593,"text":"Here you see actual data showing\ndifferent species in different colors."},{"time":611130,"text":"Reds are one type of species, blues are another,"},{"time":613270,"text":"and greens are yet another."},{"time":615615,"text":"And when we take this together and scale up"},{"time":617778,"text":"to the regional level,"},{"time":619662,"text":"we get a completely new geography"},{"time":622231,"text":"of biodiversity unknown prior to this work."},{"time":626619,"text":"This tells us where the big biodiversity changes"},{"time":628767,"text":"occur from habitat to habitat,"},{"time":630781,"text":"and that's really important because it tells us"},{"time":632964,"text":"a lot about where species may migrate to"},{"time":635859,"text":"and migrate from as the climate shifts."},{"time":638742,"text":"And this is the pivotal information that's needed"},{"time":641964,"text":"by decision makers to develop protected areas"},{"time":645472,"text":"in the context of their regional development plans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648891,"text":"And third and final question is,"},{"time":650788,"text":"how do we manage biodiversity on a planet"},{"time":652896,"text":"of protected ecosystems?"},{"time":654874,"text":"The example I started out\nwith about lions hunting,"},{"time":657625,"text":"that was a study we did"},{"time":659480,"text":"behind the fence line of a protected area"},{"time":661472,"text":"in South Africa."},{"time":663204,"text":"And the truth is, much of Africa's nature"},{"time":665202,"text":"is going to persist into the future"},{"time":667117,"text":"in protected areas like I show in blue on the screen."},{"time":670363,"text":"This puts incredible pressure and responsibility"},{"time":672839,"text":"on park management."},{"time":674458,"text":"They need to do and make decisions"},{"time":677075,"text":"that will benefit all of the species\nthat they're protecting."},{"time":680366,"text":"Some of their decisions have really big impacts."},{"time":683435,"text":"For example, how much and where"},{"time":685511,"text":"to use fire as a management tool?"},{"time":688151,"text":"Or, how to deal with a large species like elephants,"},{"time":691376,"text":"which may, if their populations get too large,"},{"time":693829,"text":"have a negative impact on the ecosystem"},{"time":695876,"text":"and on other species."},{"time":697478,"text":"And let me tell you, these types of dynamics"},{"time":699971,"text":"really play out on the landscape."},{"time":701919,"text":"In the foreground is an area with lots of fire"},{"time":704380,"text":"and lots of elephants:"},{"time":705647,"text":"wide open savanna in blue, and just a few trees."},{"time":709323,"text":"As we cross this fence line, now we're getting"},{"time":711504,"text":"into an area that has had protection from fire"},{"time":713828,"text":"and zero elephants:"},{"time":715685,"text":"dense vegetation, a radically different ecosystem."},{"time":719843,"text":"And in a place like Kruger,"},{"time":722233,"text":"the soaring elephant densities"},{"time":723974,"text":"are a real problem."},{"time":725717,"text":"I know it's a sensitive issue for many of you,"},{"time":728081,"text":"and there are no easy answers with this."},{"time":730741,"text":"But what's good is that\nthe technology we've developed"},{"time":733057,"text":"and we're working with in South Africa, for example,"},{"time":735529,"text":"is allowing us to map every\nsingle tree in the savanna,"},{"time":738885,"text":"and then through repeat flights"},{"time":740454,"text":"we're able to see which trees"},{"time":742200,"text":"are being pushed over by elephants,"},{"time":744230,"text":"in the red as you see on the screen,\nand how much that's happening"},{"time":747488,"text":"in different types of landscapes in the savanna."},{"time":750025,"text":"That's giving park managers"},{"time":751666,"text":"a very first opportunity to use"},{"time":754029,"text":"tactical management strategies\nthat are more nuanced"},{"time":757371,"text":"and don't lead to those extremes\nthat I just showed you."},{"time":762282,"text":"So really, the way we're looking"},{"time":764905,"text":"at protected areas nowadays"},{"time":766946,"text":"is to think of it as tending to a circle of life,"},{"time":769834,"text":"where we have fire management,"},{"time":771882,"text":"elephant management, those impacts on\nthe structure of the ecosystem,"},{"time":776016,"text":"and then those impacts"},{"time":778006,"text":"affecting everything from insects"},{"time":780312,"text":"up to apex predators like lions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783112,"text":"Going forward, I plan to greatly expand"},{"time":784877,"text":"the airborne observatory."},{"time":786605,"text":"I'm hoping to actually put the technology into orbit"},{"time":788772,"text":"so we can manage the entire planet"},{"time":790455,"text":"with technologies like this."},{"time":792188,"text":"Until then, you're going to find me flying"},{"time":794037,"text":"in some remote place that you've never heard of."},{"time":796540,"text":"I just want to end by saying that technology is"},{"time":799082,"text":"absolutely critical to managing our planet,"},{"time":802821,"text":"but even more important is the understanding"},{"time":804920,"text":"and wisdom to apply it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806652,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":808751,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}